 for bestpractices and # About & Help

## Overview
Create a comprehensive About & Help page for LifeOps that presents app information, documentation links, FAQ, contact support, and guided onboarding resources. The page should be designed for a dark, developer-centric UI with dense information density, strong visual hierarchy, and guided onboarding flows. It must be robust against null/undefined values, guard all array operations, and follow the runtime safety standards described in the project context.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The About & Help page of LifeOps, serving as a centralized hub for: 
  - App information (mission, company, version, privacy, terms)
  - Documentation links (getting started guides, API docs, templates)
  - FAQ (searchable, filterable)
  - Contact Support (form and status checks)
  - Guided onboarding resources (onboarding tours, checklists, templates)
  - Community links (forum, Discord/Slack)

Goals:
- Provide clear, accessible, and authoritative information about LifeOps and its modules
- Offer immediate access to documentation and onboarding resources
- Enable users to quickly contact support or check the status of tickets
- Support a guided onboarding experience that helps users learn core capabilities and best practices
- Remain consistent with LifeOps design system for typography, color palette, spacing, and components

Features connected:
- Documentation center with external/internal links
- FAQ search and filter
- Support ticket submission and status tracking
- Onboarding guides and tutorials
- Community/community-links section
- No external API dependencies required for core rendering, but ready to integrate with existing backend for tickets and onboarding status in future

UI elements and how they need to look:
- About: concise mission statement, company info, changelog, version
- Docs & Tutorials: grid/list of getting started guides, templates, API references, with badges and quick actions
- FAQ: searchable and filterable list of questions; expandable answers; top search bar
- Contact Support: form with name/email, subject, message; status panel showing recent tickets and their statuses
- Onboarding Resources: guided onboarding cards, progress indicators, checklists, and linkable steps
- Community Links: list of community channels with icons, descriptions, and invite links
- Visual guidance: consistent dark-theme surfaces, elevated cards, subtle gradient backgrounds on cards, soft glow, and clear affordances for actions

API integrations:
- No APIs connected in this task, but structure should be ready for future integration with tickets, onboarding progress, and documentation search services.

## Components to Build
- AboutHeaderCard
  - Purpose: top summary block with mission, version, and company info
  - Data: { version: string, company: string, mission: string, privacyUrl?: string, termsUrl?: string }
  - UI: bold title, subtitle, action row with links
  - Safety: guard all data access, use data ?? {} and arrays as needed
- DocumentationHubCard
  - Purpose: grid/list of documentation links and tutorials
  - Data: docs: Array<{ id, title, description, url, type, tag[] }>
  - UI: card grid with thumbnail/icon, title, short description, CTA
- FAQSearchPanel
  - Purpose: searchable FAQ
  - Data: questions: Array<{ id, question, answer, tags[] }>
  - UI: search input, filter chips, expandable items
- ContactSupportPanel
  - Purpose: support contact form and status
